## What is Node.JS
The main idea of Node.js: use non-blocking, event-driven I/O to remain lightweight and efficient in the face of data-intensive real-time applications that run across distributed devices.

In one word, NodeJS is a great tool for web development.

-  Node.js was never created to solve the compute scaling problem. It was created to solve the I/O scaling problem, which it does really well.
- Node.js really shines with real-time applications
- it’s quite a natural fit for exposing the data from object DBs
